Mitsui vice - president to join DuPont board . DuPont Co has elected Goro Watanabe , executive vice - president of Japanese trading house Mitsui & Co Ltd , as a board member , the company ' s Japanese subsidiary DuPont KK said on Wedensday . In a statement , DuPont chairman Edgar S . Woolard said : " Goro Watanabe will strengthen the global business perspective of our board . This is particularly important with the growth plans we have for the Asia - Pacific region . " Mitsui and DuPont KK set up an equally owned joint venture in 1993 to expand the marketing of DuPont products in Asia . 
